D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F67e466e1b8b41a9673fbcc03%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22720%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EA%20mobile%20phone%20map%20with%205G%20technology.%3Cp%3ET-Mobile%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3E5G's%20impact%20has%20been%20underwhelming%2C%20with%20limited%20consumer%20benefits%20and%20unmet%20promises.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EHigh%20costs%20and%20technical%20challenges%20hindered%205G's%20widespread%20adoption%20and%20network%20expansion.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EUS%20carriers%20face%20difficulties%20monetizing%205G%2C%20with%20coverage%20gaps%20and%20declining%20revenue%20per%20user.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3ERemember%20when%205G%20was%20going%20to%20change%20everything%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBack%20in%202019%2C%20wireless%20industry%20leaders%20didn't%20just%20promise%20better%20cell%20service.%20They%20promised%20a%20better%20world%20where%20doctors%20could%20operate%20on%20patients%20remotely%2C%20and%20smart%20cities%20with%20driverless%20cars%20would%20make%20roads%20safer%20and%20less%20congested.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFast%20forward%20to%20today%2C%20and%20the%20average%20consumer%20might%20be%20hard-pressed%20to%20notice%20much%20difference%20between%204G%20and%205G%20in%20their%20daily%20lives.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%220233a967-3403-44e6-b3c1-15558dc3c378%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20Hype%20Machine%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EMany%20of%20the%20most%20ambitious%20promises%20either%20didn't%20require%205G%20or%20were%20simply%20impractical.%20For%20instance%2C%20remote%20surgery%20demands%20more%20than%20just%20high-speed%20internet%3B%20it%20requires%20sterile%20environments%2C%20anesthesia%2C%20and%20willing%20patients.%20Similarly%2C%20autonomous%20vehicles%20need%20to%20function%20independently%20of%20a%20mobile%20connection%2C%20raising%20questions%20about%20the%20need%20for%205G%20to%20begin%20with.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20more%20recent%20reports%20mentioning%205G%20take%20a%20different%20tack%20%E2%80%94%20downgrading%20from%20bold%20claims%20like%20ultraconvenient%20%26quot%3Bsmart%20cities%26quot%3B%20to%205G-enabled%20drones%20that%20can%20monitor%20for%20insurance%20fraud.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%228e5469c1-9732-4a8f-a004-f611bd21da39%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20Technical%20Reality%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20of%20the%20most%20significant%20advancements%20in%205G%20is%20the%20use%20of%20higher%20frequencies%2C%20which%20carry%20more%20information%2C%20but%20don't%20travel%20as%20far.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESo%2C%20to%20use%20them%2C%20you%20need%20more%20antennas%20closer%20together%20%E2%80%94%20something%20called%20network%20densification.%20Building%20out%20the%205G%20network%20in%20the%20US%20has%20required%20hundreds%20of%20billions%20of%20dollars%20of%20investment.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETo%20cut%20costs%2C%20much%20of%20the%20early%205G%20infrastructure%20was%20built%20by%20tweaking%20existing%204G%20sites.%20This%20approach%2C%20known%20as%20non-standalone%205G%2C%20offers%20efficiency%20but%20delivers%20a%204G-like%20experience.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnother%20thing%20that%20was%20supposed%20to%20be%20really%20different%20about%205G%20was%20the%20introduction%20of%20millimeter%20waves%2C%20which%20can%20theoretically%20provide%20much%20greater%20capacity.%20They%20are%20useful%20in%20select%20locations%20where%20crowds%20really%20pack%20in%20like%20stadiums%20or%20airports.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20in%20general%2C%20the%20distance%20they%20travel%20is%20so%20short%20and%20these%20waves%20are%20so%20easily%20blocked%20that%20widespread%20use%20in%20mobile%20networks%20just%20hasn't%20made%20a%20lot%20of%20sense%2C%20and%20many%20smartphones%20don't%20even%20support%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20not%20all%20bad%20news.%20When%20phones%20are%20actually%20connected%20to%20a%205G%20network%2C%20they%20generally%20get%20faster%20speeds%20and%20lower%20latency.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20thing%20is%20that%20for%20most%20people%20and%20most%20purposes%2C%20%3Cem%3E4G%20%3C%2Fem%3Ewas%20already%20good%20enough.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECoverage%20%E2%80%94%20not%20speed%20%E2%80%94%20is%20one%20of%20the%20biggest%20problems%20we%20still%20face.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%20data-script%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20data-styles%3D%5C%22default-width%5C%22%20data-embed-type%3D%5C%22custom%5C%22%20data-type%3D%5C%22embed%5C%22%3E%3Cdiv%3E%3Ciframe%20width%3D%5C%22100%25%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%225G%20disappointed%20consumers%20and%20phone%20carriers.%20Who's%20cashing%20in%3F%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.jwplayer.com%2Fplayers%2FVHt8tOoB-puACk8ZV.html%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22100%25%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fiframe%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22c72e3986-2a40-4ff7-acfc-9af99a0ff74b%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20Coverage%20Divide%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20US%2C%20coverage%20is%20patchy%20or%20nonexistent%20in%20many%20remote%20or%20rural%20areas.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECarriers%20simply%20haven't%20built%20their%20networks%20out%20in%20a%20lot%20of%20these%20places%2C%20often%20because%20there%20aren't%20enough%20paying%20customers%20living%20there%20to%20justify%20the%20investment.%20This%20is%20part%20of%20what's%20called%20the%20%26quot%3Bdigital%20divide.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20defining%20feature%20of%205G%20is%20its%20higher%2C%20shorter-range%20frequencies.%20If%20the%20top%20priority%20was%20expanding%20coverage%2C%20building%20out%20existing%204G%20to%20more%20places%20networks%20would%20have%20been%20more%20efficient%20than%20upgrading%20so%20much%20existing%204G%20infrastructure%20in%20cities.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20you've%20ever%20seen%20a%20TV%20ad%20about%205G%2C%20then%20you%20might%20now%20be%20a%20little%20confused%20because%20the%20maps%20they%20show%20tend%20to%20make%20it%20look%20like%205G%20is%20already%20nearly%20everywhere.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDouglas%20Dawson%20has%20tested%20cellphone%20speeds%20across%20the%20country%20for%20his%20telecommunication%20consulting%20firm%2C%20CCG%2C%20and%20found%20that%205G%20only%20covers%2030%25%20to%2040%25%20of%20the%20land%20area%20in%20most%20US%20counties.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BPeople%20have%20trouble%20even%20making%20a%20cellphone%20call%20%E2%80%94%204G%20or%205G%20%E2%80%94%20because%20towers%20only%20have%20a%20limited%20circle%20around%20them%20of%20coverage%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20asked%20the%203%20major%20US%20carriers%20for%20comment%20on%20the%20accuracy%20of%20their%20maps.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOnly%20T-Mobile%20answered%20the%20question%20directly.%20%26quot%3BCoverage%20Maps%20provide%20a%20general%20service%20expectation%3B%20it's%20not%20flawless%2C%26quot%3B%20a%20spokesperson%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EUsers%20may%20see%20a%205G%20icon%20on%20their%20phones%20even%20when%20not%20connected%20to%20a%205G%20network.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.washingtonpost.com%2Ftechnology%2F2024%2F09%2F24%2F5g-phone-signal-bars-meaning-iphone-android%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EThe%20Washington%20Post%20%3C%2Fa%3Ereported%20that%2C%20in%20the%20US%2C%20the%20icon%20just%20means%20that%20a%20mobile%20network%20is%20nearby%20and%20not%20necessarily%20that%20you're%20connected%20to%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20asked%20all%20major%20US%20carriers%20about%20this%2C%20too.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAT%26amp%3BT%20said%20the%205G%20icon%20appears%20where%20the%20technology%20is%20available.%20T-Mobile%20said%20their%20icon%20is%20always%20accurate%2C%20and%20Verizon%20didn't%20get%20back%20to%20us.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%202024%20industry%20report%20showed%20that%20Verizon%20and%20AT%26amp%3BT%205G%20users%20were%20connected%20to%20a%205G%20network%20only%20about%20one-tenth%20of%20the%20time.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20is%20despite%20the%20fact%20that%20the%20US%20wireless%20industry%20has%20built%20nearly%20100%2C000%20new%20cell%20sites%20since%202018.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20no%20surprise%20that%20carriers%20amplified%20the%20hype.%20They%20invested%20an%20enormous%20amount%20of%20money%20into%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22552dc911-a516-40f6-a149-37fc74637494%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20Costly%20Reality%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20three%20major%20US%20phone%20carriers%20spent%20over%20%24100%20billion%20on%20licenses%20to%20use%20the%20frequencies.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20doesn't%20include%20the%20cost%20of%20upgrading%204G%20sites%20to%205G%20or%20of%20building%20tons%20of%20new%20cell%20sites%2C%20which%20has%20required%20billions%20%3Cem%3Emore%20%3C%2Fem%3Edollars%20in%20investment.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20they%20have%20struggled%20to%20monetize%205G%2C%20with%20monthly%20phone%20bills%20decreasing%20because%20of%20competition.%20The%20average%20revenue%20per%20user%20has%20been%20trending%20downwards%20even%20as%20investment%20from%20carriers%20has%20risen%2C%20putting%20them%20in%20a%20difficult%20position.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2237f53fea-a0bc-437a-9552-5ebd60f71eca%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20Race%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EBecause%20telecommunications%20is%20of%20massive%20economic%20and%20social%20importance%20equipment%20vendors%20%E2%80%94%20those%20who%20sell%20the%20actual%20infrastructure%20like%20antennas%20%E2%80%94%20and%20industry%20trade%20groups%20can%20lobby%20government%20officials%2C%20telling%20them%20that%20the%20next%20generation%20will%20be%20essential%20and%20transformative%20%E2%80%94%20and%20that%20if%20they%20don't%20act%20quickly%2C%20they%20might%20miss%20out%20on%20the%20benefits.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20pressure%20contributed%20to%20the%20narrative%20that%20the%20US%20and%20other%20nations%20were%20engaged%20in%20a%20global%20%26quot%3B5G%20race.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20turn%2C%20politicians%20who%20are%20most%20likely%20not%20telecoms%20engineering%20experts%20but%20might%20also%20be%20eager%20to%20implement%20new%20infrastructure%20projects%20see%20this%20as%20a%20no-risk%20position.%20Who%20wouldn't%20want%20to%20align%20themselves%20with%20the%20next%20frontier%20of%20technological%20innovation%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20rush%20could%20have%20resulted%20in%20many%20of%20these%20problems%2C%20including%20the%20decision%20to%20start%20with%20non-standalone%205G%20networks%2C%20and%20the%20the%20failure%20of%205G%20to%20differentiate%20itself%20from%204G%20in%20the%20eyes%20of%20consumers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%205G%20was%20also%20rushed%20in%20the%20planning%20phase.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDeveloping%20a%20plan%20for%20a%20new%20generation%20usually%20takes%20about%2010%20years%2C%20but%205G%20was%20rushed%20out%20in%20just%20eight.%20This%20was%20partially%20because%20of%20global%20political%20pressure%2C%20and%20because%20Japan%20planned%20a%20splashy%205G%20debut%20for%20the%202020%20Olympics%2C%20even%20though%20it%20ended%20up%20delayed%20a%20year%20due%20to%20the%20Covid-19%20pandemic.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2239c4c0f8-16d8-4cdf-bec3-053615c1dcf7%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3ELooking%20Ahead%3A%206G%20and%20Beyond%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20possible%20that%205G%20will%20be%20a%20continuation%20of%20a%20pattern%20established%20by%20previous%20networks.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20odd%20generations%20%E2%80%94%201G%20and%203G%20%E2%80%94%20were%20somewhat%20disappointing%2C%20but%20the%20even%20generations%20that%20followed%20worked%20out%20the%20kinks%20and%20had%20greater%20benefits.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESo%20we%20could%20see%20bigger%20transformations%20with%206G.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20as%20we%20get%20closer%20to%20the%20sixth%20generation%2C%20most%20experts%20Business%20Insider%20spoke%20to%20said%20it's%20on%20the%20same%20troubled%20path.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhy-5g-failed-to-change-the-world-2025-3%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1743022985000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F67e4670e69253ccddf9a659f%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwh