0group%20discussing%20plans%20of%20an%20attack%20on%20the%20Houthis%20in%20Yemen%20on%20March%2015%2C%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noindex%2Cnofollow%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.theatlantic.com%2Fpolitics%2Farchive%2F2025%2F03%2Fsignal-group-chat-attack-plans-hegseth-goldberg%2F682176%2F%5C%22%3EThe%20Atlantic%3C%2Fa%3E%20has%20shared%20the%20full%20text%20of%20the%20chats%2C%20including%20screenshots%2C%20highlighting%20that%20it%20had%20received%20very%20specific%20information%20more%20than%20two%20hours%20before%20the%20start%20of%20the%20bombing.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20information%20and%20particularly%20the%20exact%20times%20US%20aircraft%20were%20taking%20off%20for%20Yemen%2C%20the%20magazine%20emphasised%2C%20would%20have%20exposed%20American%20pilots%20and%20other%20personnel%20to%20%26quot%3Beven%20greater%20danger%26quot%3B%20if%20they%20had%20fallen%20into%20the%20wrong%20hands.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Atlantic's%20Editor%20In%20Chief%20Jeffrey%20Goldberg%20was%20inadvertently%20invited%20to%20the%20group%20chat%20on%20the%20Signal%20messaging%20app%20in%20which%20the%20bombing%20plans%20were%20being%20discussed.%20The%20chat%20reportedly%20included%20Vice%20President%20JD%20Vance%2C%20Defense%20Secretary%20Hegseth%2C%20Central%20Intelligence%20Agency%20Director%20John%20Ratcliffe%2C%20National%20Security%20Adviser%20Mike%20Waltz%2C%20Secretary%20of%20State%20Marco%20Antonio%20Rubio%2C%20Director%20Of%20National%20Intelligence%20Tulsi%20Gabbard%20and%20others.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EExplaining%20its%20rationale%20for%20putting%20out%20details%20of%20the%20chat%20in%20a%20new%20report%20on%20Wednesday%2C%20The%20Atlantic%20pointed%20out%20that%20Hegseth%20had%20claimed%20%26quot%3Bnobody%20was%20texting%20war%20plans%26quot%3B%20and%20Trump%20and%20others%20had%20said%20%26quot%3Bit%20wasn't%20classified%20information%26quot%3B.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20article%2C%20written%20by%20Goldberg%20and%20staff%20writer%20Shane%20Harris%2C%20said%20this%20presented%20a%20dilemma%20for%20The%20Atlantic.%20The%20magazine%2C%20it%20said%2C%20withheld%20specific%20information%20in%20an%20earlier%20report%20on%20weapons%20and%20the%20timing%20of%20the%20attack%20in%20keeping%20with%20its%20general%20rule%20to%20avoid%20publishing%20information%20about%20military%20operations%20that%20could%20jeopardise%20the%20lives%20of%20US%20personnel.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20statements%20by%20Hegseth%2C%20Gabbard%2C%20Ratcliffe%2C%20and%20Trump%20-%20combined%20with%20the%20assertions%20made%20by%20numerous%20administration%20officials%20that%20we%20are%20lying%20about%20the%20content%20of%20the%20Signal%20texts%20-%20have%20led%20us%20to%20believe%20that%20people%20should%20see%20the%20texts%20in%20order%20to%20reach%20their%20own%20conclusions.%20There%20is%20a%20clear%20public%20interest%20in%20disclosing%20the%20sort%20of%20information%20that%20Trump%20advisers%20included%20in%20nonsecure%20communications%20channels%2C%20especially%20because%20senior%20administration%20figures%20are%20attempting%20to%20downplay%20the%20significance%20of%20the%20messages%20that%20were%20shared%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20magazine%20said.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Atlantic%20said%20it%20asked%20various%20officials%20whether%20they%20objected%20to%20the%20full%20text%20of%20the%20chat%20being%20shared%20and%20got%20a%20response%20from%20White%20House%20Press%20Secretary%20Karoline%20Leavitt%2C%20who%20reiterated%20that%20no%20classified%20information%20was%20shared%20but%20that%20does%20not%20mean%20%26quot%3Bwe%20encourage%20the%20release%20of%20the%20conversation%26quot%3B.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThis%20was%20intended%20to%20be%20a%20an%20(sic)%20internal%20and%20private%20deliberation%20amongst%20high-level%20senior%20staff%20and%20sensitive%20information%20was%20discussed.%20So%20for%20those%20reason%20(sic)%20-%20yes%2C%20we%20object%20to%20the%20release%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20report%20quoted%20Leavitt%20as%20responding.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E'Threat%20To%20National%20Security'%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20magazine%20said%20experts%20had%20repeatedly%20told%20them%20that%20using%20a%20Signal%20chat%20for%20such%20sensitive%20discussions%20%26quot%3Bposes%20a%20threat%20to%20national%20security%26quot%3B%20and%20pointed%20out%20that%20Goldberg%20had%20received%20information%20on%20the%20attacks%20two%20hours%20before%20the%20scheduled%20start%20of%20the%20bombing.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%20this%20information%20-%20particularly%20the%20exact%20times%20American%20aircraft%20were%20taking%20off%20for%20Yemen%20-%20had%20fallen%20into%20the%20wrong%20hands%20in%20that%20crucial%20two-hour%20period%2C%20American%20pilots%20and%20other%20American%20personnel%20could%20have%20been%20exposed%20to%20even%20greater%20danger%20than%20they%20ordinarily%20would%20face.%20The%20Trump%20administration%20is%20arguing%20that%20the%20military%20information%20contained%20in%20these%20texts%20was%20not%20classified%20-%20as%20it%20typically%20would%20be%20-%20although%20the%20president%20has%20not%20explained%20how%20he%20reached%20this%20conclusion%2C%26quot%3B%20Goldberg%20and%20Harris%20wrote.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EAircraft%20Information%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAt%2011.44%20Eastern%20Time%2C%20Hegseth%20wrote%20that%20F-18s%20which%20made%20up%20the%20first%20strike%20package%20would%20launch%20at%2012.15%20ET%20and%20that%20a%20Houthi%20%26quot%3BTarget%20Terrorist%26quot%3B%20was%20expected%20to%20be%20attacked%20at%2013.45%20ET%20-%20over%20two%20hours%20after%20the%20message%20was%20sent.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPointing%20to%20the%20possible%20consequences%20of%20this%2C%20the%20magazine%20wrote%2C%20%26quot%3BIf%20this%20text%20had%20been%20received%20by%20someone%20hostile%20to%20American%20interests%20-%20or%20someone%20merely%20indiscreet%2C%20and%20with%20access%20to%20social%20media%20-%20the%20Houthis%20would%20have%20had%20time%20to%20prepare%20for%20what%20was%20meant%20to%20be%20a%20surprise%20attack%20on%20their%20strongholds.%20The%20consequences%20for%20American%20pilots%20could%20have%20been%20catastrophic.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAt%2014.10%20ET%2C%20more%20F-18s%20were%20expected%20to%20launch%20and%20the%20second%20strike%20was%20to%20start%20at%2015.36%2C%20with%20sea-based%20Tomahawk%20missiles%20also%20being%20launched%2C%20Hegseth%20wrote.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3B1410%3A%20More%20F-18s%20LAUNCH%20(2nd%20strike%20package)%26quot%3B%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%26quot%3B1415%3A%20Strike%20Drones%20on%20Target%20(THIS%20IS%20WHEN%20THE%20FIRST%20BOMBS%20WILL%20DEFINITELY%20DROP%2C%20pending%20earlier%20'Trigger%20Based'%20targets)%26quot%3B%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%26quot%3B1536%20F-18%202nd%20Strike%20Starts%20-%20also%2C%20first%20sea-based%20Tomahawks%20launched%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20defense%20secretary%20wrote.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20will%20say%20a%20prayer%20for%20victory%2C%26quot%3B%20Vice%20President%20Vance%20wrote%20soon%20after.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAt%2013.10%2C%20Waltz%20shared%20details%20of%20an%20attack%20site%2C%20apparently%20in%20Sanaa%2C%20writing%2C%20%26quot%3BThe%20first%20target%20-%20their%20top%20missile%20guy%20-%20we%20had%20positive%20ID%20of%20him%20walking%20into%20his%20girlfriend's%20building%20and%20it's%20now%20collapsed.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BExcellent%2C%26quot%3B%20Vance%20replied%2C%20and%20Waltz%20later%20sent%20a%20text%20with%20fist%2C%20fire%20and%20American%20flag%20emojis.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EDamage%20Control%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENational%20Security%20Council%20spokesman%20Brian%20Hughes%20had%20said%20on%20Monday%20that%20the%20chat%20cited%20by%20The%20Atlantic%20appeared%20to%20be%20%26quot%3Bauthentic%26quot%3B%20but%20Vance%20had%20accused%20the%20magazine%20of%20%26quot%3Boverselling%26quot%3B%20the%20story.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20scandal%20is%20being%20seen%20as%20one%20of%20the%20biggest%20challenges%20Trump%20and%20his%20administration%20have%20faced%20since%20the%20billionaire%20returned%20to%20power%20two%20months%20ago.%20There%20have%20also%20been%20calls%20for%20Hegseth%20and%20Waltz%20to%20resign%20over%20the%20leak.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAfter%20Wednesday's%20article%20was%20released%2C%20Waltz%20reiterated%20that%20no%20war%20plans%20were%20leaked%20and%20stressed%20that%20the%20bottom%20line%20was%20that%20Trump%20was%20protecting%20the%20US%20and%20its%20interests.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cblockquote%20class%3D%5C%22twitter-tweet%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%20lang%3D%5C%22en%5C%22%3ENo%20locations.%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%3Cbr%3E%5CnNo%20sources%20%26amp%3B%20methods.%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%3Cbr%3E%5CnNO%20WAR%20PLANS.%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%3Cbr%3E%5CnForeign%20partners%20had%20already%20been%20notified%20that%20strikes%20were%20imminent.%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%3Cbr%3E%5CnBOTTOM%20LINE%3A%20President%20Trump%20is%20protecting%20America%20and%20our%20interests.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%E2%80%94%20Mike%20Waltz%20(%40MikeWaltz47)%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2FMikeWaltz47%2Fstatus%2F1904888948628877756%3Fref_src%3Dtwsrc%255Etfw%5C%22%3EMarch%2026%2C%202025%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fblockquote%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BNo%20locations.%20No%20sources%20%26amp%3B%20methods.%20NO%20WAR%20PLANS.%20Foreign%20partners%20had%20already%20been%20notified%20that%20strikes%20were%20imminent.%20BOTTOM%20LINE%3A%20%C2%A0President%20Trump%20is%20protecting%20America%20and%20our%20interests%2C%26quot%3B%20Waltz%20wrote.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPress%20Secretary%20Leavitt%20also%20argued%20that%20the%20Atlantic%20had%20conceded%20that%20no%20war%20plans%20were%20released%20and%20said%20the%20story%20was%20a%20hoax.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cblockquote%20class%3D%5C%22twitter-tweet%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%20lang%3D%5C%22en%5C%22%3EThe%20Atlantic%20has%20conceded%3A%20these%20were%20NOT%20